Overview
========

All the words are analysed with dictionary form + grammatical tags. Each
tag is introduced with a "+" sign. We thus have

bijlav bijjla+N+Sg+Acc  
bådáv båhtet+V+Ind+Prs+Sg1

The tag scheme follows the Lule Saami (smj) standard and insights from
J. Wilbur's on-going work on Pite Saami

Note that you have to add the part of speech twice when you use the
derivational tag:

gieresvuodav gieres+N+Der/State+N+Sg+Acc

The main parts of speech (POS) for Pite Saami and their tags are:

| POS          | tag     |
|--------------|---------|
| noun         | +N      |
| verb         | +V      |
| adjective    | +A      |
| pronoun      | +Pron   |
| adverb       | +Adv    |
| conjunction  | +CC     |
| subjunction  | +CS     |
| postposition | +Po     |
| preposition  | +Pr     |
| numeral      | +Num    |
| interjection | +Interj |
| particle     | +Pcle   |

The nouns
=========

Here is a list of the nominal tags, given in the same order as for the
analysis. Note that the grammatical categories in parentheses can be
omitted.

|                      |                                                                |
|----------------------|----------------------------------------------------------------|
| Part of speech:      | +N                                                             |
| Number:              | +Sg, +Pl                                                       |
| Case:                | +Nom +Gen +Acc +Ill +Ine +Ela +Com +Abe +Ess                   |
| (Possessive suffix:) | +PxSg1 +PxSg2 +PxSg3 +PxDu1 +PxDu2 +PxDu3 +PxPl1 +PxPl2 +PxPl3 |

The adjectives
==============

In attributive position, the adjective is tagged simply at that:

|                 |       |
|-----------------|-------|
| Part of speech: | +A    |
| Attribute       | +Attr |

Used non-attributively, adjectives are inflected much like nouns, thus
have a similar tag set:

|                 |                                              |
|-----------------|----------------------------------------------|
| Part of speech: | +A                                           |
| (Grade:)        | +Comp, +Superl                               |
| Number:         | +Sg, +Pl                                     |
| Case:           | +Nom +Gen +Acc +Ill +Ine +Ela +Com +Abe +Ess |

The verbs
=========

Finite and infinite verb forms have quite distinct paradigms.

Finite verbs:

|                        |                                              |
|------------------------|----------------------------------------------|
| Part of speech:        | +V                                           |
| (Derivation) *example* | +Der/Pass                                    |
| Mood:                  | +Ind, +Pot, +Imprt, +Neg                     |
| Tense                  | +Prs, +Prt                                   |
| Person/Number          | +Sg1 +Sg2 +Sg3 +Du1 +Du2 +Du3 +Pl1 +Pl2 +Pl3 |

Non-Finite verbs:

|                  |                                                               |
|------------------|---------------------------------------------------------------|
| Part of speech:  | +V                                                            |
| (Derivation:)    | +Der/Pass                                                     |
| Non-finite forms | +Inf, +ConNeg, +Actio, +Ger, +PrsPrc, +PrfPrc, +VGen, +VAbess |

The pronouns
============

The personal pronouns:

|                 |                                              |
|-----------------|----------------------------------------------|
| Part of speech: | +Pron                                        |
| Subclass        | +Pers                                        |
| Person/Number   | +Sg1 +Sg2 +Sg3 +Du1 +Du2 +Du3 +Pl1 +Pl2 +Pl3 |
| Case:           | +Nom +Gen +Acc +Ill +Ine +Ela +Com +Abe +Ess |

The demonstrative, interrogative, relative and reflexive pronouns:

|                 |                                              |
|-----------------|----------------------------------------------|
| Part of speech: | +Pron                                        |
| Subclass        | +Dem, +Interr, +Rel, +Refl                   |
| Number          | +Sg, +Pl                                     |
| Case:           | +Nom +Gen +Acc +Ill +Ine +Ela +Com +Abe +Ess |

Indeclinable words
==================

These have their POS tag as their only tag:

|              |         |
|--------------|---------|
| adverb       | +Adv    |
| conjunction  | +CC     |
| subjunction  | +CS     |
| postposition | +Po     |
| preposition  | +Pr     |
| numeral      | +Num    |
| interjection | +Interj |
| particle     | +Pcle   |

